visual.name: Tachometer
visual.description:
The Tachometer is a flexible gauge that allows you to quickly convey detailed information in a way that can be intuitively understood.  Many customizable features are included to configure the look and feel as well as behavior, for example, variable start and end angles, configurable orientation, colors, labels, and axis scale.  This is an ideal visual for communicating measures against low, acceptable, and high components such as team performance against targets, error rates, test coverage, and customer satisfaction. 

YouTube video description of the visual https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C3OXdETbS9o 

GitHub with detailed descriptions of the 9 capability option groups https://github.com/ChamaraIC/Tachometer/blob/master/README.md

dataRoles.name: Y
dataRoles.description: Data field that define the value you want to plot

dataRoles.name: StartValue
dataRoles.description: Data field that define start value

dataRoles.name: EndValue
dataRoles.description: Data field that define end value

dataRoles.name: TargetValue
dataRoles.description: Data field that define target value

dataRoles.name: DisplayFilter
dataRoles.description: Hide gauge if value evaluates to zero or blank

startAngle.description: Angle in Degrees from verticle to startValue

endAngle.description: Angle in Degrees from verticle to endValue

axisScaleType.description: Scale to measure data in the gauge

thickness.description: Range1 thickness as a fraction of gauge radius
Range2 thickness as percentage of gauge radius
Range3 thickness as percentage of gauge radius

innerRadiusRatio.description: Length of target line as percentage of gauge radius

pointerSizeFactor.description: Distance to needle tip as percentage of gauge radius

baseThicknessFactor.description: Thickness of indicator base as percentage of its radius

round.description: Round label values for better visualization

count.description: Approximate count of labels to display

xOffset.description: Horizontal percent displacement of Callout Value from default position

yOffset.description: Vertical percent displacement of Callout Value from default position

xOffset.description: Horizontal percent displacement of Callout Percent from default position

yOffset.description: Vertical percent displacement of Callout Percent from default position
